@startuml composer_validation_contexts
title Composer validation contexts: internal CV vs external holdout

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam linetype ortho

class GPComposer {
  +compose_pipeline(data, data_source_context)
}

class PipelineObjectiveEvaluate {
  +evaluate(pipeline)
}

class ComposerDataSourceContext {
  +mode: ComposerDataSourceMode
  +data_producer
  +validation_blocks
}

enum ComposerDataSourceMode {
  internal_split
  external_holdout
}

class DataSourceSplitter {
  +build(data)
  +build_external_holdout(train_data, validation_data)
}

class "Regular AutoML" as RegularPath
class "Chunked ensemble AutoML" as EnsemblePath
class "InputData train" as TrainData
class "InputData common validation" as ValidationData

RegularPath --> DataSourceSplitter : build_internal_composer_data_source_context(data, cv_folds)
EnsemblePath --> DataSourceSplitter : build_external_holdout_composer_data_source_context(chunk, validation)

DataSourceSplitter --> ComposerDataSourceContext
ComposerDataSourceContext --> ComposerDataSourceMode
GPComposer --> ComposerDataSourceContext
PipelineObjectiveEvaluate --> ComposerDataSourceContext : reads train/validation folds

ComposerDataSourceContext --> TrainData
ComposerDataSourceContext --> ValidationData : external_holdout only

note right of ComposerDataSourceContext
  Before:
  composer validation was effectively tied to requirements/cv_folds.

  Now:
  runtime validation data lives in ComposerDataSourceContext.
  Chunked ensembles use a shared external validation set.
end note

@enduml
